1
00:00:00,280 --> 00:00:02,260
AWS CodeCommit Overview.

2
00:00:03,610 --> 00:00:08,470
AWS CodeCommit is a fully managed source control service in the cloud.

3
00:00:09,460 --> 00:00:13,770
It makes it easy for companies to host secure, highly scalable,

4
00:00:13,780 --> 00:00:15,420
Git-based repositories.

5
00:00:16,430 --> 00:00:19,200
CodeCommit eliminates the need to operate your own

6
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:22,940
source control system or worry about scaling its infrastructure.

7
00:00:23,520 --> 00:00:24,380
With CodeCommit,

8
00:00:24,510 --> 00:00:27,400
you can securely store anything from source code to binaries.

9
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:29,770
AWS CodeCommit

10
00:00:30,150 --> 00:00:32,870
works seamlessly with your existing Git tools.

11
00:00:34,750 --> 00:00:36,060
Here are the key benefits.

12
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:38,280
Fully managed.

13
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:42,470
AWS CodeCommit eliminates the need to host,

14
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:45,840
maintain, back up, and scale your own source control servers.

15
00:00:46,940 --> 00:00:48,600
As your project grows and the number

16
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:52,390
of your repository increases, the service automatically scales.

17
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:54,440
Secure.

18
00:00:55,370 --> 00:01:00,560
AWS CodeCommit automatically encrypts your files in transit and at rest.

19
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:05,700
CodeCommit is integrated with AWS Identity and Access Management,

20
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:11,550
or AWS IAM, allowing you to customize user-specific access to your repositories.

21
00:01:12,310 --> 00:01:17,520
With Git credentials, you can also generate a static username and password in AWS IAM

22
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:20,310
to access AWS CodeCommit repositories.

23
00:01:21,130 --> 00:01:22,440
High availability.

24
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:27,930
AWS CodeCommit has a highly scalable, redundant, and durable architecture.

25
00:01:29,180 --> 00:01:31,700
The service is designed to keep your repositories

26
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,410
highly available and accessible.

27
00:01:35,270 --> 00:01:36,400
Collaborate on code.

28
00:01:37,910 --> 00:01:41,630
AWS CodeCommit helps you collaborate on code with teammates.

29
00:01:42,650 --> 00:01:47,240
You can also implement workflows that include code reviews and feedback by default

30
00:01:47,260 --> 00:01:50,270
and control who can make changes to specific branches.

31
00:01:52,030 --> 00:01:53,710
Faster development lifecycle.

32
00:01:54,570 --> 00:01:58,790
AWS CodeCommit keeps your repositories close to your build,

33
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:02,550
staging, and production environments in the AWS Cloud.

34
00:02:03,490 --> 00:02:05,290
You can transfer incremental changes

35
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:07,310
instead of the entire application.

36
00:02:08,210 --> 00:02:12,680
This allows you to increase the speed and frequency of your development lifecycle.

37
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,030
Use your existing tools.

38
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:19,740
AWS CodeCommit supports all Git commands

39
00:02:19,860 --> 00:02:21,840
and works with your existing Git tools.

40
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,750
You can keep using your preferred development tools with CodeCommit.

